<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?><?Xpress productLine="ncc-clause" ?><clause xmlns:xt="urn:xpressauthor:trackchanges" id="_05545176-b05b-4316-99d6-1c8cbca87a27" outputclass="ncc-clause"><sptc>D3D31</sptc><title id="_b42e5855-5714-495f-9881-eba0fb27fbb0">Wayfinding signage</title><archive-num><placeholder outputclass="placeholder">[ARCHIVE]</placeholder></archive-num><subclause id="_aaf7e063-58f3-43ad-a46e-d38bee252319" outputclass="subclause"><title id="_bbaf7dcf-1665-45bc-9522-2e05322566d1">SubClause</title><num>1</num><p>Buildings with an <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/d5440ff9-b49a-4154-8539-afc815034863/1252_2.0.0.xml#_cd986c21-bc64-43a9-954d-86e35d335b74" id="_aca97ede-49a3-4275-a405-0ba164e33e42" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">effective height</xref> of more than 12 m or with more than 3 below ground <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/d5440ff9-b49a-4154-8539-afc815034863/1483_25.0.0.xml#_53ff3ea1-55e7-4f2a-b2b3-ca445ff64c15" id="_db18c2ec-fe65-48b4-90c4-3e9b58bf4b54" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">storeys</xref> must be provided with stairway identification signs, floor level identification signs and <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/d5440ff9-b49a-4154-8539-afc815034863/1473_0.4.0.xml#_d2c89488-8a36-464b-94f6-a91d0f5a6c9c" id="_1a9112a7-979f-4fd8-b6f0-20583ad9a8f0" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">sole-occupancy unit</xref> indicator signs in accordance with (2) to (6).</p></subclause><subclause id="_fbf1c4d1-7675-47d6-a027-e275c71a88f1" outputclass="subclause"><title id="_a34214b9-2d7a-4943-af66-ad4fee522298">SubClause</title><num>2</num><p>Stairway identification signs must—</p><ol outputclass="alpha"><li id="_efd22f45-e5b2-4521-8e71-9e02a574662e">be located external to the <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/d5440ff9-b49a-4154-8539-afc815034863/1263_2.3.0.xml#_9712f630-8cf7-401b-b1cc-ae0be4485915" id="_8ed30fc9-7a8c-465a-8468-c41e037090c2" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">exit </xref>on or adjacent to all doors that provide access into <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/d5440ff9-b49a-4154-8539-afc815034863/1432_4.0.0.xml#_af6fde9f-147d-4782-8b85-42044e80fd42" id="_aaba58c8-7b10-4758-8975-338d9a653d34" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">required </xref><xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/d5440ff9-b49a-4154-8539-afc815034863/1285_2.1.0.xml#_c71e675e-d6e1-4612-8e59-381a56e224a8" id="_2f4a84a8-abfd-4016-b50b-f334e77d4e24" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">fire-isolated stairways</xref>, including discharge doors; and</li><li id="_1689a96d-c879-4dd9-8dfa-5a538c582dfd">identify the floor levels served where the <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/d5440ff9-b49a-4154-8539-afc815034863/1432_4.0.0.xml#_af6fde9f-147d-4782-8b85-42044e80fd42" id="_49b50557-342a-4d54-a821-7d31ad7c9d27" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">required </xref><xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/d5440ff9-b49a-4154-8539-afc815034863/1285_2.1.0.xml#_c71e675e-d6e1-4612-8e59-381a56e224a8" id="_b18701a6-ee0d-4142-b4a2-35629933e414" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">fire-isolated stairway</xref> does not serve all floor levels; and</li><li id="_b53e03f6-1bb4-44ac-b1da-0f9841ad3e4e">state—<ol><li>“Stair”, or in the case of a scissor stair “Scissor Stair”, and</li><li>a unique stair descriptor; and</li></ol></li><li id="_7b77a4c3-9572-472f-b10f-cb3592f0abf5">use text that—<ol><li>is not less than 50 mm high; and</li><li>contrasts with its background; and</li><li>is legible in low level lighting conditions or when illuminated with a torch.</li></ol></li></ol></subclause><subclause id="_76c13ef8-4741-46e9-955b-b8bd320aacb3" outputclass="subclause"><title id="_824d2c7a-8554-4452-9689-347e756f934f">SubClause</title><num>3</num><p>Floor level identification signs must—</p><ol outputclass="alpha"><li id="_12b7471a-9911-41b7-b94a-206a6e0b2ec4">be located—<ol><li>at every landing that is located at a floor level and is in a <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/d5440ff9-b49a-4154-8539-afc815034863/1432_4.0.0.xml#_af6fde9f-147d-4782-8b85-42044e80fd42" id="_aac3452e-c9be-43f5-bf94-df2c4387c360" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">required</xref> <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/d5440ff9-b49a-4154-8539-afc815034863/1285_2.1.0.xml#_c71e675e-d6e1-4612-8e59-381a56e224a8" id="_86306144-dbe9-4cea-81c1-8def26c16623" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">fire-isolated stairway</xref>; and</li><li>at every corridor or lobby into which an emergency lift or lift with a stretcher facility opens; and</li></ol></li><li id="_a70b9d4c-ddec-41ac-8a3d-cddae48da6b6">be visible from the top step of the <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/d5440ff9-b49a-4154-8539-afc815034863/1307_2.8.0.xml#_448dd81f-b4c5-4c29-9aec-d57b83b33db5" id="_dc55dbe6-1b10-4e18-89d6-5c0bf3a5d32d" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">flight</xref> serving the relevant floor and, where possible, from inside the relevant lift where the lift car door open; and</li><li id="_5c9f9c27-84f7-4d8a-8047-08eeecafdaa5">be mounted between 1.7 m and 2 m above floor level and, as far as practicable, at the same height; and</li><li id="_6658038b-415a-40c4-a225-c99bde2c0ef0">where within a <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/d5440ff9-b49a-4154-8539-afc815034863/1432_4.0.0.xml#_af6fde9f-147d-4782-8b85-42044e80fd42" id="_45c20be4-dc1b-4a24-bc1c-616dc708875c" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">required</xref> <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/d5440ff9-b49a-4154-8539-afc815034863/1285_2.1.0.xml#_c71e675e-d6e1-4612-8e59-381a56e224a8" id="_6d6f2ba6-513f-4a8e-ad0e-7d42e3cc5ca5" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">fire-isolated stairway</xref>, identify that <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/d5440ff9-b49a-4154-8539-afc815034863/1432_4.0.0.xml#_af6fde9f-147d-4782-8b85-42044e80fd42" id="_0727a607-e088-497f-8ab3-9d2ba6bc9df5" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">required</xref> <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/d5440ff9-b49a-4154-8539-afc815034863/1263_2.3.0.xml#_9712f630-8cf7-401b-b1cc-ae0be4485915" id="_c148722e-363f-4add-8a65-9d705a59f093" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">exit</xref> stairway in accordance with (2)(c); and</li><li id="_413d968c-86c5-4772-a2d2-6c3f23600c64">state—<ol><li>“Ground Floor” when identifying the ground floor level; or</li><li>“Level”, or in the case of a basement level “Basement”, in conjunction with a floor level descriptor; and</li></ol></li><li id="_be9f6608-d921-47bd-86d2-5c65e6ba793c">use text that—<ol><li>is not less than 50 mm high, except the height of the character that designates the floor level descriptor must be at least 100 mm high; and</li><li>contrasts with the background, and</li><li>is legible in low level lighting conditions or when illuminated with a torch.</li></ol></li></ol></subclause><subclause id="_2e4774d3-8ae4-450b-b2a6-9cae1b5ef83d" outputclass="subclause"><title id="_88b8c05a-e6b2-483f-b793-32b27f4641d9">SubClause</title><num>4</num><p>The floor level descriptor <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/d5440ff9-b49a-4154-8539-afc815034863/1432_4.0.0.xml#_af6fde9f-147d-4782-8b85-42044e80fd42" id="_8b9abbe5-00e2-4b80-bbab-ff970dde5c04" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">required</xref> by (3)(e)(ii) must—</p><ol outputclass="alpha"><li id="_98d0ab38-538c-4242-92cd-c2e406927f88">for floor level above the ground floor, be numbered sequentially beginning with”1”, and</li><li id="_bbfe81e9-38fc-48e0-86f8-86daf6b1b17d">for basement levels below the ground floor, be numbered sequentially beginning with “1”.</li></ol></subclause><subclause id="_954d1cff-9878-4db4-aaf7-e7be94e7a866" outputclass="subclause"><title id="_d1842ed0-cc63-415a-8281-a29220ad70ea">SubClause</title><num>5</num><p>Where a <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/d5440ff9-b49a-4154-8539-afc815034863/1483_25.0.0.xml#_53ff3ea1-55e7-4f2a-b2b3-ca445ff64c15" id="_ee3a6ec0-9547-45ee-9106-a4ad690c9709" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">storey</xref> in a Class 2 or Class 3 building contains more than one <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/d5440ff9-b49a-4154-8539-afc815034863/1473_0.4.0.xml#_d2c89488-8a36-464b-94f6-a91d0f5a6c9c" id="_aec828f8-3b82-45d4-8ffd-48c8ee234644" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">sole-occupancy unit</xref>, <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/d5440ff9-b49a-4154-8539-afc815034863/1473_0.4.0.xml#_d2c89488-8a36-464b-94f6-a91d0f5a6c9c" id="_cdc28baa-98a0-48bd-9edc-145282f87770" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">sole-occupancy unit</xref> indicator signs must be provided that state the direction to <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/d5440ff9-b49a-4154-8539-afc815034863/1473_0.4.0.xml#_d2c89488-8a36-464b-94f6-a91d0f5a6c9c" id="_cdf387ca-7f55-4f93-9843-3ca3339acccd" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">sole-occupancy units</xref> accessed on that <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/d5440ff9-b49a-4154-8539-afc815034863/1483_25.0.0.xml#_53ff3ea1-55e7-4f2a-b2b3-ca445ff64c15" id="_79696314-5b91-45c9-9c2a-af3ef85144fa" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">storey</xref>.</p></subclause><subclause id="_3c023cfe-3a22-4ac1-b2df-fd0cbb7e1ca6" outputclass="subclause"><title id="_2393fe71-cec6-4258-8f9e-70364e053c99">SubClause</title><num>6</num><p><xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/d5440ff9-b49a-4154-8539-afc815034863/1473_0.4.0.xml#_d2c89488-8a36-464b-94f6-a91d0f5a6c9c" id="_711a9854-760b-4c62-8f9d-fdbd58ab10c6" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">Sole-occupancy unit</xref> identification signs required by (5) must—</p><ol outputclass="alpha"><li id="_37c270d6-a343-4907-ac47-8037f889228a">be located immediately below floor identification signs provided under (3)(a), such that the top edge of the sign is not more than 50 mm below the bottom edge of the floor identification sign; and</li><li id="_6153dd8b-961d-4c7d-abe8-faa8a4d372d4">state—<ol><li>“Units” or another suitable descriptor such as “Rooms” or “Apartments”; and</li><li>a sequential descriptor of the range of <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/d5440ff9-b49a-4154-8539-afc815034863/1473_0.4.0.xml#_d2c89488-8a36-464b-94f6-a91d0f5a6c9c" id="_6176dab5-d163-44f0-b2c0-f6e658c37634" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">sole-occupancy units</xref> in each direction relative to the location of the sign; and</li><li>the direction in which the range of <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/d5440ff9-b49a-4154-8539-afc815034863/1473_0.4.0.xml#_d2c89488-8a36-464b-94f6-a91d0f5a6c9c" id="_1612d014-28c3-465c-976a-0a8b0b9cd7e1" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">sole-occupancy units</xref> are relative to the location of the sign, such as by an arrow symbol; and</li></ol></li><li id="_79ab05f1-7dad-48da-8e61-290058d3b234">use text and symbols that—<ol><li>are not less than 25 mm high; and</li><li>contrast with the background; and</li><li>are legible in low level lighting conditions or when illuminated with a torch.</li></ol></li></ol></subclause><callout id="_7a22fe24-9cc4-4167-ae2e-eb7eb87b1d2c"><callout-type ncc-info-type="notes"/><ol outputclass="numbered"><li id="_b5d07b4f-da86-435a-9c56-b8c66da70bf8">Where a <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/d5440ff9-b49a-4154-8539-afc815034863/1473_0.4.0.xml#_d2c89488-8a36-464b-94f6-a91d0f5a6c9c" id="_fb367265-02c1-42e1-86e2-c3b15c21b044" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">sole-occupancy unit</xref> is accessed from 2 or more <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/d5440ff9-b49a-4154-8539-afc815034863/1483_25.0.0.xml#_53ff3ea1-55e7-4f2a-b2b3-ca445ff64c15" id="_ce91f396-30e1-41b1-9b27-dd2c2654fa92" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">storeys</xref>, the <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/d5440ff9-b49a-4154-8539-afc815034863/1473_0.4.0.xml#_d2c89488-8a36-464b-94f6-a91d0f5a6c9c" id="_0c204426-cdda-40de-9067-cf8b1032a917" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">sole-occupancy unit</xref> need only be identified by a <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/d5440ff9-b49a-4154-8539-afc815034863/1473_0.4.0.xml#_d2c89488-8a36-464b-94f6-a91d0f5a6c9c" id="_2898b8bb-8bcb-496d-84a2-dc2fe1262eca" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">sole-occupancy unit</xref> identification sign on the primary access <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/d5440ff9-b49a-4154-8539-afc815034863/1483_25.0.0.xml#_53ff3ea1-55e7-4f2a-b2b3-ca445ff64c15" id="_cbc43dd2-cb3f-4c65-b427-8b0ee2b76944" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">storey</xref>.</li><li id="_eb1ae52a-e819-499f-a40d-37e14b3f8b30">Stairway, floor level and <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/d5440ff9-b49a-4154-8539-afc815034863/1473_0.4.0.xml#_d2c89488-8a36-464b-94f6-a91d0f5a6c9c" id="_8a267585-6ceb-42f2-962c-6f29c7a62c42" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">sole-occupancy unit</xref> designations are to be consistent with designations used in block plans and other <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/d5440ff9-b49a-4154-8539-afc815034863/1299_0.4.0.xml#_0506eff4-aff6-4610-b001-ba80d4f3b9c7" id="_71e79e10-d702-4ad0-a5bf-80cfbec72ca6" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">fire safety system</xref> documentation.</li><li id="_6c43fd87-7d39-46fe-9053-2c9bc809cddb">Notwithstanding D3D31(3)(e) and D3D31(4)—<ol><li>abbreviations (such as ‘G’ for ‘Ground Floor’) may be used; and</li><li>the ground level may be identified as ‘Level 1’; and</li><li><xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/d5440ff9-b49a-4154-8539-afc815034863/1373_0.7.0.xml#_f68246d9-7a77-41fc-8050-516881323e47" id="_79e111fb-07c9-4159-b3e8-a718c5785481" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">mezzanines</xref>, split levels (such as lower ground and upper ground) and the like may be identified accordingly.</li></ol></li></ol></callout><callout id="_494256ec-8313-4815-8374-4a54e241bede"><callout-type ncc-info-type="info"/><p>Each <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/d5440ff9-b49a-4154-8539-afc815034863/1432_4.0.0.xml#_af6fde9f-147d-4782-8b85-42044e80fd42" id="_8812f860-843e-4a39-b698-7fafef3bcfda" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">required </xref><xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/d5440ff9-b49a-4154-8539-afc815034863/1285_2.1.0.xml#_c71e675e-d6e1-4612-8e59-381a56e224a8" id="_a4c4e59d-e0e8-486d-a16d-1f05dec4c501" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">fire-isolated stairway</xref> and floor level is to be provided with a unique descriptor to assist co-ordination of egress and <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/d5440ff9-b49a-4154-8539-afc815034863/1275_0.4.0.xml#_cc69b717-0915-4071-87d9-176353f8cc9a" id="_064f571d-74be-43ec-bcf7-891dfbbc0a41" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">fire brigade</xref> activities. For example, a building may be provided with 2 <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/d5440ff9-b49a-4154-8539-afc815034863/1432_4.0.0.xml#_af6fde9f-147d-4782-8b85-42044e80fd42" id="_4a373965-170f-4c65-a893-afec52713b1e" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">required </xref><xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/d5440ff9-b49a-4154-8539-afc815034863/1285_2.1.0.xml#_c71e675e-d6e1-4612-8e59-381a56e224a8" id="_1397fbec-2a3a-4f35-ba1b-ddeab05cc5fd" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">fire-isolated stairways</xref>, A and B. Stairway identification signs and floor identification signs for stairway B must contain the text “Stair B”.</p></callout></clause>